  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, the relatively modest amount stolen ($25,000), the defendant's clean prior record, and the fact that partial restitution has already been made weigh in favor of a shorter custodial sentence. A sentence of 6 months serves as a punitive measure that acknowledges the severity of the fiduciary breach while allowing for rehabilitation and the ongoing repayment of the remaining debt.",
